Mozambique Says Changes to Mining Laws Will be Applied to New Title Rights

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-07-07T14:50:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/mozambique-says-changes-to-mining-laws-will-be-applied-to-new-title-rights.html
Changes to  Mozambique ’s mining laws
will only apply to new licenses, said Mario Marques, adviser to
Mineral Resources Minister Esperanca Bias.  “Vested rights of title holders will be respected,” he
said today in an e-mailed response to questions. The government
of Mozambique considered coal, oil and gas to be “strategic.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
